This is fy_poolparty_3000a it's based of fy_poolparty_v2.
The basic idea is that you are up high in the sky on a platform, where metal and lasers are the main constructions.

I've for long played around with the thoughts of making future-version of poolparty and I finally pulled myself together and made it. 

My server is currently running it, and people seem to enjoy this map, so hopefully you will too :) 
More info on this map is on bricksite.com/agnetic

Have fun!

Welcome to Fy_Poolday_Redefined!

Credits:  All credits for original design and build go to BSODUtensil.

Being that I am completely out of ideas lately, as you can see from my last surf map, I was talking to some friends and they suggested I give a go at remaking the infamous poolday, so with that being said... here it is!

Whenever I remake a map of this popularity I try to keep as true to the original work as possible, format wise.  I don't like to change the "build" of the map more over then improve the quality of the build and the look of the map as a whole.  I believe I did just that in this map.

I took the fy_poolday_bsod_v1 and redid everything from scratch using the old file a stencil basically.

Fixes/Changes:

-New floor layout (as the old one was poorly put together)
-New brush work to give a fresh new look
-New textures
-Some minor changes to window features throughout the map
-New stairs and brush work throughout the entire center section
-Buyzone is located in the pool in the center of the map.

All in all, if you decompile this version and compare it to the original, you will see the drastic difference in brush work and "cleanliness," for lack of a better word, in the maps .vmf making it run much smoother, while also giving it a fresh new feel.

I decided to use the same guns that fy_iceworld uses to even out the sides a bit... 

Any comments/suggestions/complaints/opinions please direct to:

Xfire: wowyourgaiy
Email: Phantomoper3@comcast.net

Thanks everyone, enjoy!

This is my first map. It is built with the exact same dimensions as the original poolday map, with some graphical improvements. Also, all the weapons in counter-strike excluding flash-bangs and smoke grenades are available on this map. There is a buy-zone and bombsite on the diving board. Finally, there is only one AWP which is in the swimming pool, and one Desert Eagle on the Diving Board.

Have Fun!
---------------------------------------------------------

This map is still in a early-beta stage.

Please contact me if you want to report any bugs, ask any questions, or if I forgot to credit anyone.

23 March, 2012
==================

After working on it for some time, the second beta is now available for download! Some improvements include:
- The addition of the missing MP5 on the CT's side
- The addition of the UMP45 for both T's and CT's
- The addition of cubemaps
- Smoothed some curves
- Toned down the HDR after receiving some complaints about it being too bright
- New custom sky (by komaokc)

18 April, 2012
==================

Beta 2 Update (Update #3):

-More textures
-Added Mirror
-Map Optimization
-Edited the toilet stall doors
-Minor improvements to detail geometry

Have fun!

26 May, 2012
==================

Due to other pressing concerns, the work on this map is indefinetly suspended.

This map has HDR, so when you open it, it might look weird - If this happens, type "buildcubemaps" in console. A little cutscene will pop up, after that, exit the server and CS:S. After that, you open it again and it should work.

EDIT: I went on a LAN and some of the people that were there downloaded this map, typed "buildcubemaps", but when they made a server out of it, others couldn't join. If you don't know how to fix this, don't type in the code, because it works without it.
